<TITLE> Ex-PSC member Dr Mahfuz gets 8 years for tax dodge </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Mymensingh, Dec 10 (bdnews24.com)  A Mymensingh special court Monday sentenced Dr Mahfuzur Rahman, former member of the Public Service Commission, to eight years in jail for dodging tax. Judge Md Anisuzzaman of Mymensingh Senior Special Judge's Court handed down the verdict that also fined him Tk 58 lakh or another year behind bars. Additional tax commissioner Md Amjad Hossain of Mymensingh Tax Circle-2 on October 7 filed the first-ever tax-dodge case filed in Mymensingh under the emergency powers rules against Mahfuzur, also former dean of Bangladesh Agriculture University. The case filed at the trial court charged him with dodging payment of Tk 57.12 lakh in taxes during the 2002-2003 and 2006-2007 tax years. Mahfuz was also charged with concealing information about his having undeclared assets worth Tk 2.14 crore. The former PSC chairman in his wealth statement submitted to the Anticorruption Commission declared his possessions to be worth only Tk 7.55 lakh. The ACC on investigating his bank accounts unearthed the huge cash lying with a number of accounts maintained with Sonali Bank, Prime Bank, BRAC Bank and Pubali Bank. Mahfuz taught at Mymensingh Agriculture University from 1974 to 2002 and joined the PSC in 2002 to continue until April 2, 2007. bdnews2
